text: so very fine a young man
the son of Mr. Darcy's steward
the very noble lady whom I have the honour of calling patroness
girl with only ten thousand pounds
a young man who has lived so long in Derbyshire
a man who has not one agreeable quality
the good lady who shewed us the house
a young woman of inferior birth
the son of his late father's steward
poor Jane! who would willingly have gone through the world without believing that so much wickedness existed in the whole race of mankind, as was here collected in one individual
